stylometry: The concept of a logical upper limit is that it sets an upper bound on an model as a constraint of possible outcomes. This is important because it can set realistic expectations, such as in a decision table. We use a logical upper limit in the form of an EVPI (expected value of perfect information), which can add the realistic limitation of a budget to a model that would otherwise not use this factor when determining the best possible decision. The purpose of a logical upper limit is to make sure that the results of a model are actually useful to a company.
